  "html": "<body class=\"ParkSite\"><span aria-label=\"Top of page\" id=\"__topdoc__\" role=\"navigation\"></span>\n\n<!--googleoff: index-->\n<div id=\"beforeSkipLinks\" tabindex=\"-1\"></div>\n\n<!--googleon: index-->\n<!--googleoff: index-->\n\n<!--googleon: index-->\n<!--googleoff: index-->\n<div class=\"GlobalHeader usaGlobalHeader\" role=\"banner\">\n\n</div>\n<!--googleon: index-->\n<div aria-hidden=\"true\" aria-labelledby=\"exitModalLabel\" class=\"modal refreshableModal\" id=\"myModal\" tabindex=\"-1\">\n<div class=\"modal-dialog\">\n<div class=\"modal-content\">\n<div class=\"modal-header\">\n<h2 class=\"modal-title visually-hidden\" id=\"exitModalLabel\">Exiting nps.gov</h2>\n<button aria-label=\"Close\" class=\"btn-close\" data-bs-dismiss=\"modal\" type=\"button\"></button>\n</div>\n<div class=\"modal-body\"></div>\n\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"cs_control CS_Element_Schedule\" id=\"cs_control_481716\"><div id=\"CS_Element_BannerContainer\" title=\"\"><div class=\"cs_GridRow\" id=\"gridRow_1_1_481716\"><div class=\"cs_GridColumn\" id=\"gridCol_1_1_1_1_481716\"><div class=\"cs_control CS_Element_CustomCF\" id=\"cs_control_830326\"><div id=\"CS_CCF_1966632_830326\">\n\n</div></div><div class=\"cs_control CS_Element_CustomCF\" id=\"cs_control_481855\"><div id=\"CS_CCF_1966632_481855\"> </div></div></div></div></div></div>\n<div id=\"Park-header\">\n<div class=\"container\">\n<div class=\"pull-left\">\n<!--googleoff: index-->\n\n<!--googleon: index-->\n\n</div>\n<!--googleoff: index-->\n\n<!--googleon: index-->\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"container\">\n<div aria-label=\"Alerts Notification\" class=\"AlertsNotification\" data-site-code=\"grca\" id=\"AlertsNotification\" role=\"dialog\">\n<div aria-live=\"polite\" class=\"AlertsNotification__Status visually-hidden\" role=\"status\">Loading alerts</div>\n<div class=\"collapse\">\n<div class=\"AlertsNotification__Panel\">\n<div class=\"AlertsNotification__Header\">\n<h2 class=\"Tag\" id=\"AlertsNotificationHeading\">Alerts In Effect</h2>\n<button aria-label=\"Dismiss\" class=\"AlertsNotification__DismissButton\" type=\"button\">\nDismiss\n<svg class=\"usa-icon\" focusable=\"false\" role=\"presentation\">\n<use href=\"/theme/assets/vendor/npsds/packages/icons/dist/sprite.svg#close\"></use>\n</svg>\n</button>\n<span class=\"hr clearfix\"></span>\n</div>\n<div class=\"AlertsNotification__Body\" id=\"AlertsNotificationBody\">\n<div class=\"AlertsNotification__MoreLinkContainer\">\n<svg class=\"usa-icon\" focusable=\"false\" role=\"presentation\">\n<use href=\"/theme/assets/vendor/npsds/packages/icons/dist/sprite.svg#add\"></use>\n</svg>\n<a class=\"AlertsNotification__MoreLink\" href=\"/grca/planyourvisit/conditions.htm\" id=\"AlertsNotificationMoreLink\" tabindex=\"-1\">\nmore information on current conditions...\n</a>\n</div>\n</div>\n\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n\n<div class=\"MainContent\" id=\"main\" role=\"main\">\n\n<div aria-labelledby=\"modal-contact-us-label\" class=\"modal fade\" id=\"modal-contact-us\" tabindex=\"-1\">\n<div class=\"modal-dialog\">\n<div class=\"modal-content\">\n<div class=\"modal-header\">\n<h4 class=\"modal-title visually-hidden\" id=\"modal-contact-us-label\">Contact Us</h4>\n<button aria-label=\"Close\" class=\"btn-close\" data-bs-dismiss=\"modal\" type=\"button\"></button>\n</div>\n<div class=\"modal-body\">\n\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div id=\"adminTools\"></div>\n<div class=\"container\">\n<div class=\"ColumnGrid row\">\n<!--googleoff: index-->\n<div class=\"container\">\n\n</div>\n<!--googleon: index-->\n<div class=\"ColumnMain col-sm-12\">\n<div class=\"ContentHeader text-content-size\">\n<h1 class=\"page-title\">Fire Management</h1>\n</div>\n<div class=\"row\">\n<div class=\"col-sm-12\">\n<div class=\"cs_control CS_Element_Layout\" id=\"cs_control_2\"><table cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\" class=\"CS_Layout_Table\" id=\"cs_idLayout2\" summary=\"\" width=\"100%\"><tr class=\"CS_Layout_TR\"><td class=\"CS_Layout_TD\" id=\"cs_idCell2x1x1\">\n<div class=\"cs_control CS_Element_Custom\" id=\"cs_control_1966634\">\n<div class=\"Component ArticleTextGroup TextWrapped clearfix\">\n<figure class=\"-auto-width\">\n<picture>\n<source srcset=\"/grca/learn/management/images/BurnPic1.jpg?maxwidth=1300&amp;autorotate=false&amp;quality=78&amp;format=webp\" type=\"image/webp\"/>\n<img alt=\"a firefighter watches a low intensity forest fire\" src=\"/grca/learn/management/images/BurnPic1.jpg?maxwidth=1300&amp;autorotate=false\" title=\"A firefighter monitors a burn on the south rim of the Grand Canyon.\"/>\n</picture>\n<figcaption>A firefighter monitors a burn on the south rim of the Grand Canyon <p class=\"figcredit\">NPS Photo / J. Pennington</p></figcaption>\n</figure><!-- floating-image alignment  -->\n<p>Fire has been a part of the Colorado Plateau ecosystem for thousands of years. Its presence is important for wildlife habitat, nutrient recycling, plant diversity, and overall landscape health. Fire managers at Grand Canyon National Park seek to strike a balance between maintaining the land and protecting human life and property.<br/>\n<br/>\nDuring the past century, fire was feared and aggressively suppressed. Over time, that led to a significant and unnatural buildup of live and dead trees, pine needles, shrubs, and grasses. Not only does this buildup create risks for developments near wildland areas, but it also poses a threat to the health of the forests.<br/>\n<br/>\nFire naturally thins the forest, recycles nutrients into the soil, and stimulates new plant growth. Fire ecology research has shown that many plant and animal species benefit from the restorative effects of fire.<br/>\n<br/>\nFire managers use monitoring data and the latest fire ecology research to guide their efforts to restore the natural fire regimes at Grand Canyon National Park. Fire managers work with wildlife biologists, vegetation ecologists, historic preservation specialists, and interagency cooperators to achieve common goals of enhanced habitat and improved ecosystem functions.<br/>\n</p>\n<hr color=\"#a9a9a9\" noshade=\"noshade\" size=\"1\" style=\"text-align: left\" title=\"\"/>\n</div></div>\n<div class=\"CS_Layout_SpacingHeight\" id=\"cs_spacer_5992206\" style=\"line-height:1;\"> </div>\n<div class=\"cs_control CS_Element_Custom\" id=\"cs_control_5992206\"> \n\n<div class=\"VideoHero\" itemscope=\"\" itemtype=\"http://schema.org/VideoObject\">\n<meta content=\"Living With Fire in the Grand Canyon\" itemprop=\"name\"/>\n<meta content=\"Fire can be utilized to shape the landscape and achieve large-scale resource goals. Conversely, wildland fire can also adversely impact our resources, both natural and cultural. The Grand Canyon Fire Management Program views the wise use of fire as an important tool in the effort to reduce the impacts and restore balance to our ecosystems.\" itemprop=\"description\"/>\n<meta content=\"T4M9S\" itemprop=\"duration\"/>\n<meta content=\"https://www.nps.gov/nps-audiovideo/legacy/grca/3A09C7DC-1DD8-B71B-0B409785F7F0A07C/grca-LivingwithFireintheGrandCanyon1_splash.jpg\" itemprop=\"thumbnailUrl\"/>\n<meta content=\"https://www.nps.gov/media/video/view.htm?id=3A09C7DC-1DD8-B71B-0B409785F7F0A07C\" itemprop=\"embedURL\"/>\n<meta content=\"2020-10-14 00:00:00.0\" itemprop=\"uploadDate\"/>\n<div class=\"VideoHero-container\">\n<video class=\"video-js vjs-default-skin vjs-big-play-centered vjs-16-9\" controls=\"\" height=\"264\" id=\"av_D92B69606AD1418CAF3C62179EEAAB15\" poster=\"https://www.nps.gov/nps-audiovideo/legacy/grca/3A09C7DC-1DD8-B71B-0B409785F7F0A07C/grca-LivingwithFireintheGrandCanyon1_splash.jpg\" preload=\"metadata\" width=\"640\">\n<source label=\"720p\" res=\"720\" src=\"https://www.nps.gov/nps-audiovideo/legacy/grca/3A09C7DC-1DD8-B71B-0B409785F7F0A07C/grca-LivingwithFireintheGrandCanyon1_1280x720.mp4\" type=\"video/mp4\">\n<source label=\"480p\" res=\"480\" src=\"https://www.nps.gov/nps-audiovideo/legacy/grca/3A09C7DC-1DD8-B71B-0B409785F7F0A07C/grca-LivingwithFireintheGrandCanyon1_854x480.mp4\" type=\"video/mp4\"/>\n<source label=\"360p\" res=\"360\" src=\"https://www.nps.gov/nps-audiovideo/legacy/grca/3A09C7DC-1DD8-B71B-0B409785F7F0A07C/grca-LivingwithFireintheGrandCanyon1_640x360.mp4\" type=\"video/mp4\"/>\n<source label=\"240p\" res=\"240\" src=\"https://www.nps.gov/nps-audiovideo/legacy/grca/3A09C7DC-1DD8-B71B-0B409785F7F0A07C/grca-LivingwithFireintheGrandCanyon1_426x240.mp4\" type=\"video/mp4\"/>\n</source></video>\n<button aria-disabled=\"false\" aria-live=\"polite\" class=\"vjs-embed-control vjs-button\" data-bs-target=\"#av_D92B69606AD1418CAF3C62179EEAAB15EmbedModal\" data-bs-toggle=\"modal\" id=\"av_D92B69606AD1418CAF3C62179EEAAB15EmbedButton\" title=\"Embed Video\" type=\"button\">Embed</button>\n<div aria-hidden=\"true\" aria-labelledby=\"av_D92B69606AD1418CAF3C62179EEAAB15EmbedModalLabel\" class=\"modal fade VideoJSEmbedModal\" id=\"av_D92B69606AD1418CAF3C62179EEAAB15EmbedModal\" tabindex=\"-1\">\n<div class=\"modal-dialog modal-dialog-centered\">\n<div class=\"modal-content\">\n<div class=\"modal-header\">\n<h1 class=\"modal-title\" id=\"av_D92B69606AD1418CAF3C62179EEAAB15EmbedModalLabel\">\nEmbed Video\n</h1>\n<button aria-label=\"Close\" class=\"btn-close\" data-bs-dismiss=\"modal\" type=\"button\"></button>\n</div>\n<div class=\"modal-body\">\n<textarea class=\"form-control\" id=\"av_D92B69606AD1418CAF3C62179EEAAB15EmbedText\" rows=\"6\"></textarea>\n</div>\n\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n\n<div class=\"VideoHero-text\">\n<a class=\"VideoHero-videoLink visuallyhidden\" href=\"/media/video/keyboard-shortcuts.htm\">Visit our keyboard shortcuts docs for details</a>\n<dl class=\"result-details wrapped\">\n<dt>Duration:</dt><dd>4 minutes, 9 seconds</dd>\n</dl>\n<p itemprop=\"description\">Fire can be utilized to shape the landscape and achieve large-scale resource goals. Conversely, wildland fire can also adversely impact our resources, both natural and cultural. The Grand Canyon Fire Management Program views the wise use of fire as an important tool in the effort to reduce the impacts and restore balance to our ecosystems.</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"CS_Layout_SpacingHeight\" id=\"cs_spacer_1966638\" style=\"line-height:1;\"> </div>\n<div class=\"cs_control CS_Element_Custom\" id=\"cs_control_1966638\">\n<div class=\"Component ArticleTextGroup TextWrapped clearfix\">\n<figure class=\"-left\">\n<picture>\n<source srcset=\"/grca/learn/management/images/BurnPic3.jpg?maxwidth=650&amp;autorotate=false&amp;quality=78&amp;format=webp\" type=\"image/webp\"/>\n<img alt=\"a firefighter watches piles of fuel burning\" src=\"/grca/learn/management/images/BurnPic3.jpg?maxwidth=650&amp;autorotate=false\" title=\"A firefighter monitors a pile burn in Grand Canyon National Park\"/>\n</picture>\n<figcaption><p class=\"figcredit\">NPS Photo / J. Pennington</p></figcaption>\n</figure><!-- floating-image alignment  -->\n<p><strong>Fire Education</strong> <strong>QUICKLINKS:</strong><br/>\n<a href=\"https://www.nwcg.gov/about-the-nwcg-glossary-of-wildland-fire\" id=\"CPNEWWIN:NewWindow^top=10,left=10,width=500,height=400,toolbar=1,location=1,directories=0,status=1,menubar=1,scrollbars=1,resizable=1@https://www.nwcg.gov/glossary/a-z|\" onmouseout=\" return window.status=''; \" onmouseover=\" return window.status='https://www.nwcg.gov/glossary/a-z'; \">Wildland Fire Glossary</a><br/>\n<a href=\"https://www.nps.gov/fire/wildland-fire/learning-center/educator-resources/fire-education.cfm\" id=\"CPNEWWIN:NewWindow^top=10,left=10,width=500,height=400,toolbar=1,location=1,directories=0,status=1,menubar=1,scrollbars=1,resizable=1@https://www.nps.gov/fire/educational/education.cfm\" onmouseout=\" return self.status=''; \" onmouseover=\" return self.status='https://www.nps.gov/fire/educational/education.cfm'; \">NPS Fire Education Portal</a><br/>\n<br/>\n<br/>\n<strong>Fire Effects Monitoring - Air Quality</strong><br/>\n<a href=\"https://www.nps.gov/subjects/air/webcams.htm?site=grca\" id=\"https://www.nps.gov/subjects/air/webcams.htm?site=grca|\">Grand Canyon Visibility - WEBCAM</a><br/>\n<a href=\"https://cms.nps.gov/articles/airprofiles-grca.htm\" id=\"CP___PAGEID=5912888,airprofiles-grca.htm,30335|\">Air Quality Profile - Grand Canyon National Park</a><br/>\n<br/>\n<br/>\n<strong>Fire Management Documents:</strong><br/>\n<a href=\"https://parkplanning.nps.gov/projectHome.cfm?projectId=10959\" id=\"https://parkplanning.nps.gov/projectHome.cfm?projectId=10959|\">Grand Canyon Fire Management Plan</a><br/>\n<a href=\"javascript:HandleLink('cpe_0_0','CPNEWWIN:NewWindow^popup=1,top=10,left=10,width=500,height=400,toolbar=1,location=1,directories=0,status=1,menubar=1,scrollbars=1,resizable=1@https://parkplanning.nps.gov/');\" id=\"CPNEWWIN:NewWindow^popup=1,top=10,left=10,width=500,height=400,toolbar=1,location=1,directories=0,status=1,menubar=1,scrollbars=1,resizable=1@https://parkplanning.nps.gov/|\" onmouseout=\" return window.status=''; \" onmouseover=\" return window.status='https://parkplanning.nps.gov/'; \">NPS Park Planning Documents</a> Open for public comment<br/>\n<br/>\n<br/>\n<strong>Fire Ecology Research</strong><br/>\n<a href=\"https://cms.nps.gov/grca/learn/nature/research_permits.htm\" id=\"CP___PAGEID=2005693,/grca/learn/nature/research_permits.htm,14077|\">Obtaining a Grand Canyon National Park Research Permit</a><br/>\n<a href=\"https://cms.nps.gov/grca/learn/nature/research_grants.htm\" id=\"CP___PAGEID=2005707,/grca/learn/nature/research_grants.htm,14077|\">Opportunities for research collaboration</a><br/>\n<br/>\n<br/>\n<strong>Find the latest research articles from our partners at:</strong><br/>\n<a href=\"https://nau.edu/forestry/internal-resources/master-of-forestry-professional-papers/\" id=\"https://nau.edu/forestry/internal-resources/master-of-forestry-professional-papers/|\">Northern Arizona University - School of Forestry</a><br/>\n<a data-bs-target=\"#myModal\" data-bs-toggle=\"modal\" data-remote=\"/common/commonspot/customcf/modals/modal_intercept.cfm?targetURL=https%3A%2F%2Fnau.edu%2FERI%2F\" data-target=\"#myModal\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"https://nau.edu/ERI/\" id=\"http://www.eri.nau.edu/|\">Northern Arizona University - Ecological Restoration Institute</a></p>\n</div></div>\n</td></tr>\n</table></div>\n</div><!-- col-sm-12 -->\n</div><!-- row -->\n</div><!-- ColumnMain col-sm-9 -->\n</div><!-- ColumnGrid row -->\n</div><!-- end container -->\n<div class=\"container\">\n<div class=\"ColumnGrid row\">\n<div class=\"ColumnMain col-sm-12\">\n<div class=\"row\">\n<div class=\"col-sm-12 text-content-size text-content-style\">\n<p style=\"text-align:right;\">Last updated: July 15, 2025</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<!--googleoff: index-->\n <!-- ParkFooter -->\n<!--googleon: index-->\n\n</div><!-- end of <div main> -->\n<!--googleoff: index-->\n\n<!--googleon: index-->\n<!-- the rest of the scripts are leftovers from before the centennial down and should be pared down where possible -->\n\n<link href=\"/common/commonspot/templates/assets/libs/colorbox/colorbox.css\" rel=\"stylesheet\"/>\n\n<div class=\"modal fade\" id=\"outdated-browser\" role=\"dialog\" tabindex=\"-1\">\n</div>\n</body>",
